🧠 Python OOP Learning Lab
This repository contains my hands-on practice projects while learning Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) in Python.

The goal of this repository is not to build production-ready software, but to deeply understand how real-world systems are structured using classes, objects, and system design principles.

🚀 What I Learned
Through these exercises, I practiced and improved my understanding of:

Classes and Objects
Constructors (__init__)
Encapsulation (public, protected, private variables)
Methods and object behavior
State management
Object-to-object interaction
Basic system design thinking
Logging systems (in-memory and file-based)
Timestamp usage in transactions

🏦 Project Example: Bank Account System
One of the main exercises is a Bank Account Simulation System, which includes:

Deposit and withdrawal operations
Transfer between accounts
Transaction history tracking
File-based logging system
Timestamped transaction records

This project simulates how real banking systems track user actions internally.

📂 Project Structure
python-oop-learning-lab/
│
├── bank_account.py
├── transaction.txt (ignored in real usage)
└── README.md

🎯 Purpose of This Repository
This repository is part of my learning journey in software development.

It helps me:

Build strong foundations in Python OOP
Think like a backend developer
Prepare for internship opportunities
Develop problem-solving and system design skills

